codex
The full backend suite exposed one deliberate compatibility decision: management profile reads were already a public global contract. I preserved that by making `members.member.read` an explicit global scope alongside the two checker permissions—still independent of role provenance or unowned rows—while member updates remain owner-scoped. The prior implicit behavior is now named and reviewable.
