 | A-067 | The member registration/edit surface is isolated in `MemberGovernanceForm` while using only the existing card, field, alert, button, grid, colour, spacing, and typography classes. | Registration and reasoned identity correction have shared state/payload/error behavior and no existing component can express that form without duplicating it across Directory and Profile; the binding design rules require recording an absolutely-required new component. | `docs/working/FRONTEND_DESIGN_RULES.md`; existing `MemberDirectory.tsx` and `MemberProfile.tsx` patterns | 006Y2 | Low | No | 2026-07-12 | This is a composition boundary, not a new visual system; do not add bespoke styles or generalize it beyond governed member mutations. |
 | A-068 | `members.member.identity_change.approve` is seeded as a dedicated high-risk permission with no default role assignment; administrators must explicitly grant it to the checker role selected by governance. | M02-FR-012 requires approval and 006Y3 forbids a hard-coded approver role, while the source permission catalogue does not assign a named identity-change checker. | `docs/source/functional-spec.md` M02-FR-012; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §12.2, §17-§18; `docs/slices/006Y3-member-registry-and-identity-change-approval-closure.md` | 006Y3 | High | Yes | 2026-07-12 | The requester must also differ from the approver; add a default role grant only when governance names that role. |
 | A-069 | Witness correction uses `members.witness.update` and application-scoped `GET/PATCH .../witnesses/{witness_id}/`. Name may be corrected by an authorised actor; PAN/Aadhaar correction additionally requires a different actor from the stored verifier. Verification member/shareholding/folio/qualified fact/verifier/time remain immutable. | S09 permits witness identity/display capture and the slice requires correction plus maker-checker where verification changes, but the source permission catalogue/path and approval resource are silent. A narrow update code and verifier separation close the governed mechanism without assigning a hard-coded role or rewriting verification evidence. | `docs/source/screen-spec.md` S09; `docs/source/data-model.md` §10.5, §29-§30; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §12.2, §15.4, §26.4, §34; `docs/slices/006Y4-witness-correction-and-resource-action-closure.md` | 006Y4 | High | Yes | 2026-07-12 | If governance defines a formal witness-change approval case or canonical permission/path, version the adapter while preserving optimistic locking, protected values, masked evidence, and immutable verification provenance. |
+| A-072 | `members.member.read`, `members.active_status.verify`, and `members.member.identity_change.approve` are explicit row-independent member-global scopes for their narrowly named actions. System/custom role provenance and an unowned Member never grant scope; ordinary member update remains creator-owned until assigned/team scope is persisted. | The source requires explicit permissions and global/assigned/team/created-by object categories but does not name a default role or persisted member assignment table. Treating these dedicated permissions as reviewable global scopes preserves the management read contract and permits independent maker-checker actions without hard-coded role bypasses, while denying unrelated writes. | `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §§3-3.1, §§18-19, §25.1, §34.2; `docs/slices/006Z9-active-member-authority-and-decision-contract-closure.md` | 006Z9 and future member-assignment governance | High | Yes | 2026-07-13 | If governance persists member/team assignments or narrows any action permission, update the projection and public matrices without using role provenance or caller flags. |
